Bean Lifecycle Management: @PostConstruct and @PreDestroy:

Spring manages the entire lifecycle of a bean, from creation to destruction.

a. @PostConstruct:
Purpose: Marks a method to be called after the bean is created and dependencies are injected.
Usage: For initialization logic (e.g., opening a connection, setting up resources).
Example:

@Component
public class EmailService {
    @PostConstruct
    public void init() {
        System.out.println("EmailService initialized!");
    }
}

b. @PreDestroy:
Purpose: Marks a method to be called before the bean is destroyed (when the application context is closed).
Usage: For cleanup logic (e.g., closing connections, releasing resources).
Example:

@Component
public class EmailService {
    @PreDestroy
    public void cleanup() {
        System.out.println("EmailService is being destroyed!");
    }
}
